                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4 Steering Committee/557: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-05-28T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 28, 1937—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received May 28—7:43 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1084. Supplementing my 1083, May 27, 7 p.m., Eden told me last night that after
                    talking to Stevenson he had given orders to amend the British draft speech in a
                    sense more in conformity with ours but would still have to say that Great
                    Britain was willing to put into effect publicity on national defense expenditure
                    if the other powers so desired.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
